
Overview of noun sneer

The noun sneer has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) sneer, leer -- (a facial expression of contempt or scorn; the upper lip curls)
2. sneer -- (a contemptuous or scornful remark)

Overview of verb sneer

The verb sneer has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) sneer -- (express through a scornful smile; "she sneered her contempt")
2. (1) sneer -- (smile contemptuously; "she sneered at her little sister's efforts to play the song on the piano")
